  "commentary": "With SPX at 6598.48 sitting between the max negative gamma at 6590 (-7485M) and max positive gamma at 6605 (+13913M), dealers are in active hedging mode as we approach the massive +13913M wall just 7 points above. The PIN regime combined with this tight 15-point range between max negative/positive gamma levels creates a strong magnetic pull toward 6605, where dealers will aggressively sell rallies to hedge their long gamma exposure. The 1125% 1-minute GEX surge indicates rapidly shifting option flows, but the heavy positive gamma concentration at 6605-6610 should cap upside momentum.\n\nKey levels: 6590 downside support (dealers buy dips) and 6605 resistance (dealers sell rallies), with 6638 flip strike as the regime boundary.\n\nBottom line: expect price to gravitate toward 6605 with limited upside past that level.",
